  "text": "The characterization of brain mechanisms engaged in cases of straightforward diagnosis may lead to the development of experimental protocols to study the diagnosis of clinical cases of greater complexity that calls on greater diagnostic expertise. One important element that is missing in our experiments is the active investigative process that occurs during a diagnostic assessment. Our experimental design was not planned to directly address questions related to the existing theoretical models of diagnostic reasoning in the domain of cognitive psychology [CITATION_1] 55 . Instead, we focused on hypotheses not explicitly included in these models.",
